article.headline: Wright St. 59, Detroit 58
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Vaughn Duggins hit a jumper with 4.3 seconds left as Wright State beat Detroit 59-58 Wednesday night on its way to an 11th straight victory. Duggins led all scorers with 19 points in a game that saw eight lead changes. Scottie Wilson added 14 for the Raiders (20-6, 12-4 Horizon League), who held on despite being outplayed by the Titans in the second half after pulling to a 30-23 halftime lead. With the win, Wright State assured itself at least a tie for second place in the Horizon League. Chris Hayes and Zach Everingham had 14 points apiece for Detroit (7-19, 3-13), which shot 42 percent from the field. Wright State shot 43.5 percent.
